  bugFacts:
  - "It\u2019s me, earthworm! As I tunnel through the soil and consume it, I turn
    it into rich and crumbly ground."
  - 'Tough, resilient, and thrive in almost any environment--that''s me, the ant.
    I also carry seeds to my home to help them spread. '
  - "I\u2019m black-headed cockchafer larva. I aerate the soil when I'm little, doing
    my good deed, but wait till I grow up, then I feast on root."
  - Hi, I'm yellow trapdoor spider, an architect of the soil. I build my burrow and
    hunt pests underground.
  - "Hi, I'm a pseudoscorpion. Don't let my small size fool you\u2014I'm a carnivore!"
  - Hi, I'm a dragon springtail, the cleaner of the soil! I eat fungi and decaying
    plants, speeding up the decomposition rate of organic matte.
